solution.text:
The number of oscillations per second is called the frequency of oscillation.
Number of oscillations in \(\frac1{_{k}_}\)th of a second \(=_{j}_\)
Therefore, number of oscillations in one second \(=_{k}_ \times _{j}_\)
\(=_{{j*k}}_\)
Therefore, frequency of the object \(=_{{j*k}}_\,Hz\)

content.text: If an object oscillates \(_{j}_\) times in \(\frac1{_{k}_}\)th of a second, what is its frequency?
